item.description:
This is the code used in rstudio to make barplots using the lahman dataset.
extracting the data&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;-
query&lt;- &ldquo;SELECT playerID,sum(HR) as career_HR,sum(SO) as career_SO FROM Batting GROUP BY playerID HAVING sum(HR)&gt;=400&rdquo;
result&lt;- sqldf(query)
visualizing the data&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;
ggplot()+ geom_point(data=result,aes(x=career_SO,y=career_HR,color=&ldquo;blue&rdquo;))+ ggtitle(&ldquo;Career Strikeouts VS Homeruns for Great Hitters&rdquo;)+ xlab(&ldquo;Career Strikeouts&rdquo;)+ ylab(&ldquo;Career Homeruns&rdquo;)
